{"lemma":"سَكْتَة","slug":"سَكْتَة","root":"س.ك.ت","root_slug":"س-ك-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20195","n20196","n20197"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a single interval of silence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a certain pause in recitation observed between the first and second verses of the Qur'an"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stoppage, interruption"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"apoplexy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from سَكَتَ (sakata, “to become silent”)."},"ipa":["/sak.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20195","headword_ar":"سَكْتَةٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single state of silence, muteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speechlessness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilojubolaY SaroxapN","text_ar":"لِلْجُبْلَى صَرْخَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a sakotapN","text_ar":"ثُمَّ سَكْتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To the pregnant"},{"kind":"text","text":"woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is attributable a vehement cry, then a silence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b2-  In prayer,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A silence"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pause"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the commencement;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after what precedes the first recitation of the Opening Chapter of the Kur-án;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] which is approved: and, in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the ending of the recitation of the Opening Chapter of the Kur-án."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1390},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakotN","text_ar":"سَكْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which a person loses his powers of speech and motion"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known among the physicians;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apoplexy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus called in the present day:] accord. to some, the word in this sense should be written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikotapN","text_ar":"سِكْتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mode"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stillness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but this is incorrect, being at variance with the authority of transmission. (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also the next paragraph:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sik~iytN","text_ar":"سِكِّيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20196","headword_ar":"سُكْتَةٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikotapN","text_ar":"سِكْتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one silences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hushes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiets, a child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other person;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) [generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lullaby of any kind for a child:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat remaining in a bag or other receptacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of food."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu sukotapN liEiyaAlihi","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ سُكْتَةٌ لِعِيَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakotapN","text_ar":"سَكْتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not any food with which to silence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet his family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20197","headword_ar":"سِكْتَةٌ","root":"skt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakata","text_ar":"سَكَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Silence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwtN","text_ar":"سُكُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a subst.;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukotapN","text_ar":"سُكْتَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakotapN","text_ar":"سَكْتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}